title: NOAA, Predicted Hannah storm surge along Carolinas, 6AM Sep 05 2008, South-East USA
name: NOAA, Predicted Hannah storm surge along Carolinas, 6AM Sep 05 2008, South-East USA
description:
The poly shapefile shows predicted storm surge of five ft or more than a normal tide due to tropical storm Hannah's landfall along South and North Carolina coasts.
 
The data is based on NOAA's 6 AM forecast on 5th Sept, 2008, generated by NOAA's SLOSH model (Sea, Lakes, and Onverland surge due to Hurricanes). 
http://www.nhc.noaa.gov/HAW2/english/storm_surge.shtml

Search elsewhere on Finder! an updated storm surge shapefile with keyword "Hannah"

author.source: NOAA's SLOSH model (Sea, Lake and Overland Surge due to Hurricanes)
